                            <comment id="478410" author="gerrit" created="Fri, 14 Nov 2025 23:37:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;Patrick Farrell &amp;lt;pfarrell@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&quot; uploaded a new patch: &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/62539&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/62539&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
Subject: &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19481&quot; title=&quot;FLR-EC: Basic do-no-harm lov IO support&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19481&quot;&gt;LU-19481&lt;/a&gt; lov: skip parity mirrors for normal read/write IOs&lt;br/&gt;
Project: fs/lustre-release&lt;br/&gt;
Branch: master&lt;br/&gt;
Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: d6b55f67ab17298345365952239b1169a670b255&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="476645" author="paf0186" created="Wed, 29 Oct 2025 22:53:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;With the shift to ec-as-mirror, we get most of this for free.&#160; We should still do some testing probably, but there&apos;s one thing remaining.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19527&quot; title=&quot;FLR-EC: Never select EC mirror as primary for write or allow setting PREFER flags&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19527&quot;&gt;LU-19527&lt;/a&gt; will prevent selecting a parity/EC mirror as write destination, but it could still be selected for read.&#160; In that case, we can&apos;t read from the parity components and must switch to another mirror.&#160; This is probably almost the same code as the patch which makes old clients avoid components with unknown patterns (The one referenced in &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19520&quot; title=&quot;FLR-EC: Don&amp;#39;t read parity components on old clients&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-19520&quot;&gt;LU-19520&lt;/a&gt; ), just here it would avoid components with PARITY set.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
